50|$|The Steadfastness and Confrontation Front {{should not}} be {{confused}} with the Rejectionist Front, a gathering of radical Palestinian factions outside the framework of <b>the</b> <b>PLO.</b> These factions had left <b>the</b> <b>PLO</b> after Fatah pushed through the Ten Point Program in 1974. The Steadfastness and Confrontation Front and its conflict with Egypt assisted in healing the rift between <b>the</b> <b>PLO</b> leadership <b>and</b> those supporting the Rejectionist Front.|$|R
