25|$|Ceaușescu's Romania was {{the only}} Eastern Bloc country that {{retained}} diplomatic relations with Israel and did not sever diplomatic relations after Israel's pre-emptive strike against Egypt {{at the start of}} the Six-Day War in 1967. Ceaușescu made efforts to act as a mediator between <b>the</b> <b>PLO</b> <b>and</b> Israel.|$|E
